FOOT AND MOUTH DISEASE - UGANDA: (NAKASEKE), BOVINE, REQUEST FOR INFORMATION
****************************************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Sat 29 Aug 2015
Source: NTV (Uganda) [edited]
http://www.ntv.co.ug/news/health/29/aug/2015/foot-and-mouth-disease-enters-nakaseke-8363#sthash.TlVnS5NW.dpbs


Foot and mouth disease has spread to Nakaseke from Nakasongola district, and so far about 800 head of cattle in 5 sub-counties have been affected since the start of August 2015.

Nakaseke district has approved a supplementary budget of 5 million Ugandan shillings [USD 1373.00] towards the treatment, but the Veterinary Office says it needs, and had requested, Shs 30 million [USD 8241.76].

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[Information on the serotype involved is requested.

FMD is endemic in Uganda; since 2000, the following serotypes have been recorded: O, A, SAT2, and SAT3 (all 3 SAT types are probably endemic in the African buffalo population).

For further background, please refer to Mod.CRD's commentary in archived posting 20140729.2640533. - Mod.AS

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map can be accessed at: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=3611875,97.]
